"Seltzer G., Rodbell D., Burns S.","Isotopic evidence for late Quaternary climatic change in tropical South America",2000,"Geology","28","1",,"35","38",,,10.1130/0091-7613(2000)28<35:IEFLQC>2.0.CO;2,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-84879888784&partnerID=40&md5=2a4f3318d9a904318def3a6ee69f05f7","Department of Earth Sciences, Syracuse University, Syracuse, NY 13244, United States","Seltzer, G., Department of Earth Sciences, Syracuse University, Syracuse, NY 13244, United States; Rodbell, D., Department of Earth Sciences, Syracuse University, Syracuse, NY 13244, United States; Burns, S., Department of Earth Sciences, Syracuse University, Syracuse, NY 13244, United States","The tropical hydrologic cycle affects atmospheric trace gases and global climate change, and thus records of hydrologic change encompassing a variety of time scales from the low latitudes are important in paleoclimatology. Isotopic analysis of calcite from Lake Junin, Peru, provides a record of hydrologic variability that spans the last glacial-interglacial transition in the southern tropics. The record reveals a 6‰ enrichment in δ18Ocalcite during the late glacial followed by a gradual depletion during the Holocene, which can be interpreted as a decrease followed by a long-term increase in effective moisture. Close agreement between δ18Ocalcite and rainy season insolation indicates that long-term changes in tropical hydrology were linked to orbital variations. Furthermore, hydrologic change was out of phase in the northern and southern tropics over this time period.","Andes; Carbonates; Climate change; Insolation; Lakes; Stable isotopes","calcite; climate change; Holocene; isotopic composition; lacustrine deposit; paleoclimate; Pleistocene; Quaternary; Peru",,,,,,"Abbott, M., Binford, M.B., Brenner, M.W., Kelts, K., A 3500 14C yr high resolution record of lake level changes in Lake Titicaca, South America (1997) Quaternary Research, 47, pp. 169-180; Abbott, M., Seltzer, G.O., Kelts, K., Southton, J., Holocene paleohydrology of the tropical Andes from lake records (1997) Quaternary Research, 47, pp. 70-80; Berger, A., Long-term variations of daily insolation and Quaternary climate changes (1978) Journal of Atmospheric Science, 35, pp. 2362-2367; Berger, A., Long-term variations of caloric insolation resulting from the Earth's orbital elements (1978) Quaternary Research, 9, pp. 139-167; Berger, A., Loutre, M.F., Insolation values for the climate of the last 10 million years (1991) Quaternary Science Reviews, 10, pp. 297-317; Clapperton, C.M., Hall, M., Mothes, P., Hole, M.J., Still, J.W., Helmens, K.F., Kuhry, P., Gemmell, A.M.D., A Younger Dryas ice-cap in the equatorial Andes (1997) Quaternary Research, 47, pp. 13-28; Cobbing, E.J., Pitcher, W.S., Wilson, J.J., Baldock, J.W., Taylor, W.P., McCourt, W., Snelling, N.J., The geology of the Western Cordillera of Northern Peru (1981) Great Britain Institute of Geological Sciences, , Natural Environment Research Council, 143 p; Colinvaux, P.A., De Oliveira, P.E., Moreno, J.E., Miller, M.C., Bush, M.B., A long pollen record from lowland Amazonia: Forest and cooling in glacial times (1996) Science, 274, pp. 85-88; Cross, S.L., Baker, P.A., Seltzer, G.O., Fritz, S.C., Dunbar, R.B., A new estimate of the Holocene lowstand level of Lake Titicaca, and implications for tropical paleohydrology (1999) The Holocene, , in press; Gonfiantini, R., Panichi, C., Tongiorgi, E., Isotopic disequilibrium in travertine deposition (1968) Earth and Planetary Science Letters, 5, pp. 55-58; Hammarlund, D., Aravena, R., Barnekow, L., Buchardt, B., Possnert, G., Multi-component carbon isotope evidence of early Holocene environmental change and carbon-flow pathways from a hard-water lake in Northern Sweden (1997) Journal of Paleolimnology, 18, pp. 219-233; Hansen, B.C.S., Wright H.E., Jr., Bradbury, J.P., Pollen studies in the Junín area, Central Peruvian Andes (1984) Geological Society of America Bulletin, 95, pp. 1454-146